fields.work_description: An experienced Technical Lead/Software Engineer specializing in Web-Based software with experience in the entire lifecycle of software development including gathering requirements, system design, prototypes, implementation, testing and deployment.

Lead a team of three developers working on enterprise level data centric web based applications.

  • Work with Business Analysts and customers to refine requirements and provide technical direction.
  • Mentor junior developers.
  • Refine coding standards and ensure adherence amongst the team members.
  • Maintain product backlogs and audit burndown rates to ensure successful delivery of software releases.
  • Work with Product Support and Quality Assurance departments to ensure timely release of product.

Architect and Develop enterprise web applications utilizing a wide variety of tools and methods.

  • Work closely with Build team to ensure compatibility with CM and deployment practices.

  • Work closely with Team leads to ensure accuracy of Product Backlog and adherence to Agile practices.

  • Architected several reusable components which directly ensure more efficient development across teams

  • Picked for the Product's architecture team to develop Application Shell and Framework to promote modularization of a complex system.

  • Developed DHTML Framework for integration with Application Shell.

  • Chosen as lead UI person on architecture team.

Lead web-based software development project efforts for highly successful Scheduling software company.

  • Developed reusable GUI components to streamline development efforts and increase team member efficiency.

  • Successfully developed and deployed pioneer client application for integrating with US Navy training systems(CeTARS).

  • Developed proof of concept application for US Navy readiness assessment to be conducted electronically.

Gathered requirements and conducted high level system design for several large-scale government related projects. Developed ASP.NET applications for the County of Ventura, CA.

  • Delivered system design for Automated Disease Surveillance System.

  • Developed Proof of Concept ASP.NET application for the County's Hospital Diversion Program.

  • Performed architectural upgrades and design modifications to existing successful nursing referral program for the county's public health department.

Developed web based applications. Managed conversion of legacy accounting system to web-based version.

  • Successfully installed and configured Macromedia Generator during first week of employment, a task that had gone unsuccessfully completed for 3 months.

  • Converted all data and system configurations from Legacy Platypus Software to Bill-max software. Converted Data from one schema to another while preserving relationships and maintaining data integrity.

  • Developed Flash 5 based Golf Course explorer.

Developed web based applications. Gathered customer requirements and generated system designs. Maintained Server environment for 50 web-hosting clients. Maintained databases in SQL Server and MySQL.

  • Developed and implemented online hosting account creation and signup system, enabling instant turn around on hosting orders and directly lowering operating costs.

  • Developed Unix program to handle auto-creation of Apache Virtual Hosts, including creation of DNS records, databases, log files and entries into legacy accounting system whereby lowering both cost and manpower requirements for adding new websites to server.
Developed commercial websites under the direction of the Executive Director.

Routinely transcribe foreign languages; operate sophisticated computer-assisted information systems; prepare technical and statistical reports.

  • Fully qualified Aircrewman for EP-3E aircraft.

  • DLPT (Defense Language Proficiency Test) L2/R2 for Mandarin Chinese
